The paper deals with list decoding of error-correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves probabilistic arguments and analysis of the distribution of list sizes, which are common in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper may also be relevant to complexity theory (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR), as list decoding is a fundamental problem in these areas. Finally, the paper discusses applications to rank-metric codes, which are used in coding theory and communication systems (cs.SI).
